Follow-on-Mastodon Extension Privacy Policy


Last modified: November 08, 2018


SUMMARY:
  - The extension only transmits to the server you specify.
  - The extension only transmits when the Follow on Mastodon button is clicked.
  - The extension transmits as little information as possible.
  - The extension stores no information except your preferrences.
  - See sections 4 and 5 for details on an INFORMATION LEAK RISK.


1. DEDICATION TO PRIVACY

If you have any questions or concerns relating to the privacy of this
extension, please email the author at <me@duckie.co> or open an issue
on GitHub <https://github.com/duckinator/follow-on-mastodon/issues>.

ANY storage or transmission of information not acknowledged by this policy
is either a bug or should be added to this policy.

If you notice this occuring, please contact the author as mentioned above.


2. CONTEXT AND DEFINITIONS

MASTODON
  - A social network with servers on many different domains.

PREFERRED INSTANCE
  - The domain you want to follow other Mastodon users from.
  - Configured in the extension preferences.

FOLLOW BUTTON
  - The primary button added by the Follow-on-Mastodon extension.

CURRENT URL
  - The URL for the page being viewed when the FOLLOW BUTTON is clicked.


3. INFORMATION COLLECTION AND STORAGE

ABSOLUTELY NO DATA is collected by the extension.

The only information stored is your PREFERRED INSTANCE.


4. INFORMATION TRANSMISSION

Limitations on information transmission:

- Information is ONLY transmitted to your PREFERRED INSTANCE.
- Information is ONLY transmitted when you click the FOLLOW BUTTON.
- Information is limited to a portion of the CURRENT URL.
- Information is never transmitted to the author.

All requests made by the extension include portions of the CURRENT URL
at the time the FOLLOW BUTTON was clicked.

For example, if you are viewing <https://example.org/@foo/bar> and click
the FOLLOW BUTTON, the extension will make a request including "foo" and
"example.org".

5. INFORMATION LEAK RISK

The information sent is intended to be the username for the account
you intend to follow.

However, the extension can never be completely sure the URL you are
viewing is on a Mastodon server.

Thus, if used on a non-Mastodon website, your PREFERRED INSTANCE will
still receive a portion of the CURRENT URL.
